snippet.textDisplay: One time I went to New York to see him perform and meet him. Meeting him was very disappointing, he had little enthusiasm and I even brought up that I went to the same high school as him and I brought my ID to even show him but he really did not care. I just felt like he was thinking so highly of himself he couldn’t give a genuine reaction. Or maybe that was his genuine reaction, that he just doesn’t care. I would think he’d care more since he’s now profiting off the high school we went to with his new show or whatever. He also was not very funny on stage. It was all old jokes that the whole audience already had memorized and were repeating with him. The guy before him was hilarious though so that made my night, I never laughed so hard. But yeah, Fluffy left a really bad impression on me. I don’t get the hype.
